CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 6, 1952, pg. 30, reads: "Thanksgiving Baskets for Needy - The Missionary Society of Calvary Baptist Church, 2424 Wylie Avenue, distributed baskets to the needy on Thanksgiving Day. Aiding the group in supplying the baskets were the following ministers: The Rev. R. W. Twigg of Monumental Baptist Church, the Rev. J. S. Nesbit, the Rev. J. B. Campbell of Union Baptist Church, the Rev. W. L. Harris of Oakmont Baptist Church, the Rev. J. W. Rogers of Burton Street Baptist Church, and the Rev. D. W. Bass of Carter Chapel Christian Methodist Episcopal Church.  Tyson's Bakery on Centre Avenue and Crystal Super Market on Sheridan Avenue also contributed. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Two women standing behind cornucopia filled with fruit and baskets of food, for Thanksgiving food donation to needy, by Missionary Society of Calvary Baptist Church, another version
